article.headline: N.C.-Asheville 82, Radford 63
article.story: ASHEVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Kenny George scored 17 points and North Carolina Asheville remained perfect in Big South play by beating Radford 82-63 on Wednesday night. Reid Augst added 14 points and five players reached double figures for the Bulldogs (15-4, 4-0), which has won 20 of 25 games dating to last season. K.J. Garland and Bryan Smithson each scored 12 points and Vincent James added 10 for UNC Asheville, which shot 64 percent and made 7-of-11 attempts from 3-point range. Martell McDuffy led all scorers with 19 points for Radford (5-14, 0-4). Joey Lynch-Flohr finished with 13 points and Amir Johnson added 10 for the Highlanders, who shot 40 percent and were outrebounded 36-24.
